WEBVTT

00:05.005 --> 00:09.108
<i>The Island of Sodor is
the home of the North Western Railway...</i>

00:11.478 --> 00:14.413
<i>with engines of all shapes</i>

00:14.448 --> 00:16.648
<i>and sizes...</i>

00:16.683 --> 00:21.953
<i>working hard to deliver goods and
passengers to their destinations.</i>

00:21.988 --> 00:23.789
<i>There are branch lines</i>

00:23.824 --> 00:26.391
<i>that run along the coast
of the island,</i>

00:26.426 --> 00:29.895
<i>serving the docks,
the fishing villages</i>

00:29.930 --> 00:31.696
<i>and the seaside towns.</i>

00:33.733 --> 00:38.637
<i>There are branch lines
that run to the farms, quarries</i>

00:38.672 --> 00:41.940
<i>and ancient castles
of the island's heartlands.</i>

00:43.477 --> 00:45.877
<i>And there is the main line...</i>

00:45.912 --> 00:49.815
Express coming through!

00:49.850 --> 00:53.785
<i>which runs all the way from Knapford
on the west coast of the island...</i>

00:55.489 --> 00:57.656
<i>to Vicarstown in the east.</i>

00:57.691 --> 01:01.426
<i>And the line
continues over the Vicarstown Bridge,</i>

01:01.461 --> 01:04.096
<i>where it connects
to the mainland beyond.</i>

01:09.302 --> 01:12.771
<i>One day, Henry was pulling
a very important goods train</i>

01:12.806 --> 01:14.873
<i>on his way to the mainland.</i>

01:17.077 --> 01:18.977
Faster! Faster!

01:19.012 --> 01:20.312
Hurry up, Henry!

01:20.347 --> 01:22.414
We haven't got all day!

01:25.051 --> 01:27.853
<i>A faulty signal
should have warned Henry</i>

01:27.888 --> 01:31.289
<i>there was another goods train
stuck on the track up ahead.</i>

01:31.324 --> 01:33.258
<i>Then...</i>

01:33.293 --> 01:35.427
<i>everything happened at once.</i>

01:36.796 --> 01:41.466
No!

01:41.501 --> 01:43.202
Oof!

01:49.409 --> 01:51.543
Help! Aaah!

01:53.113 --> 01:56.982
Aaah!

02:00.253 --> 02:03.488
<i>Poor Henry wouldn't
be going to the mainland now.</i>

02:03.523 --> 02:05.023
Oh!

02:07.000 --> 02:13.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

03:19.466 --> 03:21.233
Whoo-hoo!

03:21.268 --> 03:24.202
Hoo-hoo! Whoo! Ha ha ha!

03:24.237 --> 03:27.305
Hello, bunnies.
Hello, squirrels.

03:27.340 --> 03:29.874
Hello, birds.
Hello, trees.

03:29.909 --> 03:31.443
Hello, sky.

03:31.478 --> 03:32.677
Morning, Thomas.

03:32.712 --> 03:34.713
Good morning, Toby.

03:35.949 --> 03:37.282
Hi, Thomas!

03:37.317 --> 03:39.451
Thomas!

03:39.486 --> 03:42.220
Ah, what a lovely day.

03:42.255 --> 03:44.356
It's bright and sunny,

03:44.391 --> 03:47.025
and everybody on Sodor
seems happy.

03:47.060 --> 03:51.596
Don't days like this make you
feel like bursting into song?

03:51.631 --> 03:54.833
♪ <i>Somebody has
to be The favorite</i> ♪

03:54.868 --> 03:57.369
♪ <i>The one that everybody</i>
<i>Wants to see</i> ♪

03:57.404 --> 03:58.359
James!

03:58.371 --> 04:01.273
♪ <i>Somebody has to be
Better than the rest</i> ♪

04:01.308 --> 04:04.509
♪ <i>Somebody has to be so good</i>
<i>That they're the best</i> ♪

04:04.544 --> 04:07.646
♪ <i>Somebody has to be</i>
<i>The favorite</i> ♪

04:07.681 --> 04:10.882
♪ <i>Somebody has to be me</i> ♪

04:10.917 --> 04:14.586
Here's James!

04:14.621 --> 04:16.954
You're not the favorite, James.

04:16.990 --> 04:20.591
Of course I am, Thomas.
Ask anybody.

04:20.627 --> 04:22.594
No, you're not.

04:22.629 --> 04:26.631
And anyway, I was going to
sing a song then, not you.

04:26.666 --> 04:29.467
Oh, well, go ahead and
sing if you want to.

04:29.502 --> 04:31.469
I'm not stopping you.

04:31.504 --> 04:33.305
Quiet, everybody!

04:34.407 --> 04:37.042
- Huh?
- Huh?
-Huh?

04:37.077 --> 04:39.711
Thomas wants to sing a song.

04:39.746 --> 04:42.080
Oh. No, James.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.649
I-I'm not...

04:46.986 --> 04:49.788
Oh, okay.

04:52.025 --> 04:54.459
- ♪<i> Sometimes you have to
Blow your whistle</i> ♪ -

04:54.494 --> 04:58.229
♪ <i>To let the
other engines Know you're near</i> ♪

04:58.264 --> 05:01.399
♪ <i>Sometimes you have to make</i>
<i>A racket and to shout</i> ♪

05:01.434 --> 05:04.502
♪ <i>In order to ensure that
They're not left In any doubt</i> ♪

05:04.537 --> 05:07.172
♪ <i>Somebody has to be</i>
<i>The favorite</i> ♪

05:07.207 --> 05:10.041
♪ <i>Say hello</i>
<i>The favorite is here</i> ♪

05:10.076 --> 05:11.543
Hello, James!

05:13.079 --> 05:16.414
You're not Sir Topham Hatt's
favorite engine, James!

05:16.449 --> 05:20.452
Really? Then how come I keep
getting all the best jobs?

05:20.487 --> 05:24.222
Isn't your next job collecting
pigs from Farmer Trotter's?

05:24.257 --> 05:25.990
Yes.

05:26.025 --> 05:29.027
Want to know what
my next job is? But...

05:29.062 --> 05:33.665
Well... My next job is
transporting beautiful music.

05:33.700 --> 05:35.700
That's not true.

05:35.735 --> 05:37.402
You're just making that up.

06:00.693 --> 06:02.193
Bring it up. Oh!

06:02.228 --> 06:04.195
Okay. Oh. Ah.

06:04.230 --> 06:06.364
Keep coming.

06:06.399 --> 06:07.799
Nice and easy.

06:09.803 --> 06:11.770
Turn around. Set it down.

06:11.805 --> 06:13.205
- Oh.
- You're good.

06:14.274 --> 06:16.107
Oh, dear.

06:16.142 --> 06:19.077
Well, thank goodness
nobody was hurt.

06:19.112 --> 06:22.313
That's all I can say.

06:22.348 --> 06:27.218
That's right. Expect Henry to be
arriving at the Steamworks shortly.

06:27.253 --> 06:31.156
Edward is already at Vicarstown
collecting him with the breakdown train.

06:31.191 --> 06:34.092
Oh, I'm
used to swapping engines around.

06:34.127 --> 06:36.294
It's what I do all the time.

06:36.329 --> 06:39.898
I'll find another
engine to take James's passenger coaches,

06:39.933 --> 06:43.101
and he can collect those cars
first thing in the morning.

06:43.136 --> 06:46.304
I bet James won't like that job.

06:46.339 --> 06:48.140
James doesn't like pulling cars.

06:55.949 --> 06:57.982
Guess what, James.

06:58.017 --> 07:01.152
You're going to be pulling a
goods train tomorrow morning.

07:01.187 --> 07:05.056
While I will be working
with my faithful coaches again,

07:05.091 --> 07:07.158
Annie and Clarabel.

07:07.193 --> 07:08.860
Naturally.

07:08.895 --> 07:10.995
As usual.

07:11.030 --> 07:15.033
A goods train?

07:15.068 --> 07:18.236
A... Oh, wait.

07:18.271 --> 07:22.006
You must mean that very
important goods train

07:22.041 --> 07:24.042
that's bound for the mainland!

07:26.346 --> 07:28.613
That's a <i> great</i> job, Thomas.

07:28.648 --> 07:30.748
What an adventure!

07:30.783 --> 07:33.852
♪ <i>Somebody has to be</i>
<i>The favorite</i> ♪

07:33.887 --> 07:37.055
♪ <i>That's just the way it is</i>
<i>You must agree</i> ♪

07:37.090 --> 07:40.291
♪ <i>Some get to see the world</i>
<i>And travel far away</i> ♪

07:40.326 --> 07:43.495
♪ <i>While other engines Have a
place They always have to stay</i> ♪

07:43.530 --> 07:46.598
♪ <i>Somebody has to be</i>
<i>The favorite</i> ♪

07:46.633 --> 07:54.172
♪ <i>Somebody has to be me</i> ♪

07:56.843 --> 08:00.011
Oof. Don't even
listen to him, Thomas.

08:00.046 --> 08:01.980
He's only teasing.

08:02.015 --> 08:03.548
Again!

08:05.084 --> 08:06.451
Ah, right. Thank you.

08:06.486 --> 08:08.486
It's not fair, sir!

08:08.521 --> 08:11.623
James gets
all the important jobs!

08:11.658 --> 08:14.859
Important jobs?
What important jobs?

08:14.894 --> 08:18.162
Are you talking about taking
that goods train to Bridlington?

08:18.197 --> 08:21.032
Is Bridlington a place
on the mainland?

08:21.067 --> 08:25.370
Yes, Thomas, it is. But that's
hardly the only important job.

08:25.405 --> 08:28.673
What about the Flying Kipper?
Or the mail train?

08:28.708 --> 08:30.808
Or delivering the milk?

08:30.843 --> 08:33.977
Or collecting passengers
from the cruise ships?

08:34.013 --> 08:36.681
I know, sir. But James says...

08:36.716 --> 08:41.019
Even looking after your branch
line is an important job, Thomas.

08:41.054 --> 08:43.488
Now, if you'll excuse me,

08:43.523 --> 08:47.492
I have some important jobs
of my own to attend to.

08:47.527 --> 08:51.829
What with Henry out of action and
James off to the mainland tomorrow,

08:51.864 --> 08:55.934
who can I get to deliver
those cheese vats to Vicarstown?

08:59.005 --> 09:01.005
<i>That night in the sheds,</i>

09:01.040 --> 09:04.609
<i>Thomas was still very cross
about James.</i>

09:04.644 --> 09:08.012
It's just so annoying, Percy.

09:08.047 --> 09:11.349
He keeps saying he's Sir
Topham Hatt's favorite engine.

09:11.384 --> 09:15.820
And tomorrow he's going off to the
mainland to have a big adventure,

09:15.855 --> 09:20.058
while I'm stuck here
doing the same jobs I always do.

09:20.093 --> 09:21.993
Percy.

09:22.028 --> 09:25.363
You're not even listening.
Oh, I am, Thomas.

09:25.398 --> 09:28.099
But I have to take
the mail train now.

09:29.636 --> 09:32.704
It's not fair.

09:32.739 --> 09:35.506
♪ <i>Some get to see the world</i>
<i>And travel far away</i> ♪

09:35.541 --> 09:39.177
♪ <i>While other engines Have a
place They always have to stay</i> ♪

09:39.212 --> 09:42.814
Why can't I go to the mainland?

09:42.849 --> 09:47.585
<i>But then, an idea
flew into Thomas's funnel.</i>

09:51.090 --> 09:56.094
<i>The next morning, James went to Vicarstown
Goods Yard to collect his cars.</i>

09:57.296 --> 09:59.497
Rosie, where are my cars?

09:59.532 --> 10:02.266
- What have you done with them?
- Uh...

10:02.301 --> 10:04.669
Which cars do you mean, James?

10:04.704 --> 10:08.773
The cars that Henry was pulling
when he had his accident.

10:08.808 --> 10:12.910
Sir Topham Hatt said it was very important
to take them to the mainland today.

10:12.945 --> 10:15.013
Oh, those cars.

10:15.048 --> 10:17.448
Yes. I know
those cars are important.

10:17.483 --> 10:19.150
That's why Thomas came so early.

10:19.185 --> 10:20.585
Thomas?

10:20.620 --> 10:22.787
What's Thomas got to do with it?

10:22.822 --> 10:26.057
♪ <i>Sometimes you have to</i>
<i>Get up early</i> ♪

10:26.092 --> 10:29.227
♪ <i>If there's someplace</i>
<i>You really want to be</i> ♪

10:29.262 --> 10:32.463
♪ <i>Sometimes you have to be</i>
<i>Awake before the dawn</i> ♪

10:32.498 --> 10:35.600
♪ <i>Sometimes you're up and out</i>
<i>Before they know you're gone</i> ♪

10:35.635 --> 10:38.770
♪ <i>Somebody has to be</i>
<i>The favorite</i> ♪

10:38.805 --> 10:42.006
♪ <i>And this time</i>
<i>It's going to be me</i> ♪

10:42.041 --> 10:50.815
♪ <i>This time</i>
<i>It's going to be me</i> ♪

10:50.850 --> 10:53.118
Are we there yet?

10:54.520 --> 10:56.954
<i>Meanwhile, poor Henry</i>

10:56.989 --> 10:59.857
<i>was in the Steamworks
waiting to be repaired.</i>

10:59.892 --> 11:02.593
Oh, dear, oh, dear.

11:02.628 --> 11:05.163
How long do you expect him
to be out of action?

11:05.198 --> 11:07.298
He's taken my train, sir!

11:07.333 --> 11:10.168
Oh, yes! That's what he's done!

11:10.203 --> 11:13.805
Who's taken what train? What on
earth are you talking about, James?

11:13.840 --> 11:16.641
Thomas.
I'm talking about Thomas.

11:16.676 --> 11:19.177
He's taken my goods train, sir.

11:19.212 --> 11:21.846
The one that had to go
to the mainland.

11:21.881 --> 11:23.681
That's excellent.

11:23.716 --> 11:27.285
Then you can work on Thomas's
branch line today, James.

11:27.320 --> 11:29.854
Thomas's branch line?

11:29.889 --> 11:32.857
But you said
I was going to the mainland.

11:32.892 --> 11:34.492
That was my job.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.361
Well, it's my job
to swap engines around.

11:37.396 --> 11:39.997
- Yes, I know.
- That's what a railway controller does.

11:40.032 --> 11:41.666
Well, yeah, of course, but...

11:41.701 --> 11:43.835
He keeps all his engines busy...
What if...

11:43.870 --> 11:45.636
being useful.

11:45.671 --> 11:46.704
Huh? Huh?

11:46.739 --> 11:48.873
Now, who can I get

11:48.908 --> 11:52.310
to take all those coconuts
back to Arlesburgh?

11:52.345 --> 11:54.612
Oh.

11:56.682 --> 11:59.083
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

11:59.118 --> 12:00.785
Whoo-hoo!

12:03.089 --> 12:05.690
Hoo!
<i>Meanwhile on the mainland,</i>

12:05.725 --> 12:07.692
<i>Thomas was having an adventure.</i>

12:11.697 --> 12:13.197
Wow!

12:13.232 --> 12:15.666
Look at that big building
over there.

12:15.701 --> 12:18.169
I wonder
what that factory makes.

12:18.204 --> 12:22.406
Oh, did you
see the color of those houses?

12:22.441 --> 12:24.776
Bright blue!

12:24.811 --> 12:28.079
Nobody on Sodor would paint
their house bright blue.

12:28.114 --> 12:30.281
What are you
going on about, Thomas?

12:30.316 --> 12:33.484
Everything.
Just look around you.

12:33.519 --> 12:35.787
We're on the mainland now.

12:35.822 --> 12:39.423
Ooh. What's so special
about the mainland?

12:39.458 --> 12:42.160
It's all just grass and trees
as far as I can see.

12:42.195 --> 12:45.596
Lucky you. All I can see
is another truck's backside.

12:46.866 --> 12:49.867
There are lots of new things
to see here.

12:49.902 --> 12:53.004
The buildings are different
and the bridges and the...

12:53.039 --> 12:54.772
Oh, look.

12:54.807 --> 12:57.708
I wonder what junction
that is up ahead?

12:57.743 --> 13:00.278
I'd say it's Lostville.

13:00.313 --> 13:02.079
Maybe it's Confusington.

13:02.114 --> 13:04.081
Castle Who-knows-where.

13:04.116 --> 13:06.751
I'm not lost, you silly trucks.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.697
Off-the-map Central.

13:08.721 --> 13:10.621
I know exactly where I'm going.

13:10.656 --> 13:12.790
But do you know where you are?

13:12.825 --> 13:14.625
He's trying to be important.

13:14.660 --> 13:16.961
Is it
important to go the wrong way?

13:16.996 --> 13:18.707
Go left. Don't listen to him.

13:18.731 --> 13:20.965
He's facing backwards.
Turn right!

13:21.000 --> 13:23.201
Would you all please be quiet?

13:25.404 --> 13:27.471
Are we there yet?

13:31.143 --> 13:33.311
- Use your brain.
- He doesn't have one.

13:33.346 --> 13:35.413
Stop trying to confuse me.

13:35.448 --> 13:38.616
Whoa! You're
distracting the driver!

13:38.651 --> 13:40.218
Huh?

13:40.253 --> 13:41.519
Whoa.

13:49.528 --> 13:52.430
Slow down! Oh!

13:52.465 --> 13:55.633
- Slow down, James, slow down!
- Slow down, James, slow down!

13:55.668 --> 13:58.069
The faster I go,
the sooner I can get back

13:58.104 --> 14:01.038
and ask Sir Topham Hatt
for a better job!

14:01.073 --> 14:04.909
- A better job?
- A better job?

14:06.345 --> 14:09.413
Hello, Maithewaite!

14:12.084 --> 14:13.084
Oh!

14:16.789 --> 14:20.424
James! You've stopped
beyond the platform again!

14:21.928 --> 14:24.228
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

14:25.865 --> 14:29.433
I know, I know.
It was an accident, okay?

14:29.468 --> 14:32.270
I do hope Thomas gets back soon.

14:32.305 --> 14:33.971
So do I.

14:34.006 --> 14:36.974
What are you all
muttering about back there?

14:37.009 --> 14:39.010
I <i> can</i> hear you, you know.

14:41.714 --> 14:44.582
<i>But Thomas was
far away on the mainland,</i>

14:44.617 --> 14:48.052
<i>and he wasn't going to be back
anytime soon.</i>

14:48.087 --> 14:53.624
You know, I still can't believe
how I tricked James this morning.

14:53.659 --> 14:56.827
And I still can't believe we haven't
reached that goods yard yet.

14:56.862 --> 15:00.665
I can.

15:00.700 --> 15:02.233
Are we there yet?

15:02.268 --> 15:05.236
I know it's taking a bit longer
than I thought,

15:05.271 --> 15:07.972
but why don't you relax
and enjoy the journey?

15:08.007 --> 15:09.974
It can't be that much further.

15:10.009 --> 15:11.375
Halt!

15:11.410 --> 15:13.110
Aaah!

15:15.548 --> 15:17.415
What's the big idea?

15:17.450 --> 15:20.285
Who goes there?

15:21.420 --> 15:23.254
Hello there.

15:23.289 --> 15:26.057
Is this Bridlington Goods Yard?

15:26.092 --> 15:27.292
Bridlington?

15:28.828 --> 15:30.227
No!

15:30.262 --> 15:32.296
Bridlington's miles from here.

15:32.331 --> 15:35.967
Oh. But am I at least
going the right way?

15:36.002 --> 15:38.669
How should I know?
Sometimes I go back here.

15:38.704 --> 15:40.871
Whoo-hoo!

15:40.906 --> 15:43.908
And sometimes I go up here.

15:46.445 --> 15:51.215
And I can spin around and look at
the view from every direction.

15:51.250 --> 15:54.585
Ow! But I've never been to Bridlington.
What's it like, eh?

15:54.620 --> 15:56.954
- Don't ask him.
- He hasn't been there either.

15:56.989 --> 15:59.390
And at this rate,
he's never going to get there!

16:00.793 --> 16:03.094
Oh, these trucks
are very annoying!

16:03.129 --> 16:05.162
But they're right.

16:05.197 --> 16:07.865
Please, Mr. Crane.
I really have to keep going.

16:07.900 --> 16:09.900
And why exactly
should I let you go?

16:09.935 --> 16:12.236
You haven't even answered
my question yet.

16:12.271 --> 16:14.472
Question? Wh-What question?

16:14.507 --> 16:16.507
Who goes there?

16:16.542 --> 16:20.444
Meaning, who... are... you?

16:20.479 --> 16:23.314
Oh. I'm Thomas.

16:23.349 --> 16:24.648
Thomas?

16:24.683 --> 16:25.883
Who's Thomas?

16:26.786 --> 16:27.885
Hmm.

16:30.122 --> 16:31.689
♪ <i>Thomas? You're Thomas?</i> ♪

16:31.724 --> 16:33.491
♪ <i>Well, I don't know</i>
<i>Who Thomas is</i> ♪

16:33.526 --> 16:36.961
♪ <i>So why should I Let this Thomas
Simply hurry on his way?</i> ♪

16:36.996 --> 16:38.429
♪ <i>Thomas? You're Thomas?</i> ♪

16:38.464 --> 16:40.164
♪ <i>Speak up now I'm asking you</i> ♪

16:40.199 --> 16:41.899
♪ <i>Who's Thomas? What's Thomas?</i> ♪

16:41.934 --> 16:43.768
♪ <i>What have you got to say?</i> ♪

16:43.803 --> 16:45.369
♪ <i>I'm Thomas I'm a tank engine</i> ♪

16:45.404 --> 16:47.405
♪ <i>I'm from a place</i>
<i>Called Sodor</i> ♪

16:47.440 --> 16:50.085
♪ <i>I'm heading for the goods yard
Where these trucks Are meant to go</i> ♪

16:50.109 --> 16:52.243
- Mm-hmm. -♪<i> I don't know
why I'm stopped here</i> ♪

16:52.278 --> 16:53.978
♪ <i>Apart from the thing</i>
<i>You dropped here</i> ♪

16:54.013 --> 16:57.748
♪ <i>So if you could</i>
<i>Lift it up again</i> ♪

16:57.783 --> 17:00.084
♪ <i>Oh, what do you</i>
<i>Want to know?</i> ♪

17:00.119 --> 17:02.153
♪ <i>He's lost, he's lost</i> ♪

17:02.188 --> 17:04.255
♪ <i>And Thomas is his name</i> ♪

17:04.290 --> 17:05.756
♪ <i>He wanted to be important</i> ♪

17:05.790 --> 17:07.223
♪ <i>Now he's only himself</i>
<i>To blame</i> ♪

17:16.402 --> 17:17.968
♪ <i>Thomas? Who's Thomas?</i> ♪

17:18.002 --> 17:19.470
♪ <i>I've never heard of Thomas</i> ♪

17:19.505 --> 17:20.871
- Nor me.
- I know.
-You're me.

17:20.906 --> 17:22.772
That's true.
♪ <i>I'm talking to myself</i> ♪

17:22.808 --> 17:24.675
