If my cars have been delivered
to Bridlington,

32:02.620 --> 32:05.088
then my very important job
has been completed,

32:05.123 --> 32:07.424
so I need to head back to Sodor.

32:07.459 --> 32:11.494
But we helped you deliver your
goods cars, little tank engine.

32:11.529 --> 32:14.397
Surely, you don't mind
helping us in return.

32:14.432 --> 32:16.967
Well, okay.

32:17.002 --> 32:19.202
I suppose I... Whoa!

32:22.440 --> 32:24.975
You're too kind.

32:32.283 --> 32:35.819
<i>Thomas was put
to work in the steelworks,</i>

32:35.854 --> 32:37.854
<i>shunting ladle cars...</i> Ready!

32:37.889 --> 32:40.891
<i>and taking molten slag out
to the slag heaps.</i> I got it!

33:07.185 --> 33:10.653
Cinders and ashes?

33:10.688 --> 33:12.756
Good job, Thomas!

33:12.791 --> 33:15.225
He is good, isn't he?

33:15.260 --> 33:18.862
In fact, I'd say he might be
my favorite new engine.

33:24.302 --> 33:27.871
♪ <i>This is</i>
<i>The hottest place in town</i> ♪

33:27.906 --> 33:30.473
♪ <i>You really warm me up</i>
<i>When I'm feeling down</i> ♪

33:30.508 --> 33:31.719
♪ <i>This is the hottest place...</i> ♪
Whoa!

33:31.743 --> 33:33.643
Watch out there!

33:35.246 --> 33:37.447
Everybody, run!
Get out of the way!

33:37.482 --> 33:39.182
Aaah! Don't go near it!

33:39.217 --> 33:42.419
You need to be careful with that stuff.
It's very hot.

33:42.454 --> 33:44.921
It can melt your wheels
right into the ground.

33:47.792 --> 33:48.992
Sorry.

33:51.529 --> 33:53.630
<i>Oh, dear, oh, dear.</i>

33:53.665 --> 33:56.266
What a mess. Oh.

33:56.301 --> 33:58.335
Oh. Gaaah!

34:00.138 --> 34:01.805
Oh, boy.

34:01.840 --> 34:04.507
Never mind, sir. It's only tea.

34:04.542 --> 34:06.109
We'll soon clear it up again.

34:08.112 --> 34:10.013
Oh, Thomas.

34:12.183 --> 34:16.018
<i>Now arriving at Platform
5 is the Great Wooden Special.</i>

34:16.054 --> 34:18.021
Any news about Thomas, sir?

34:18.056 --> 34:20.690
No, Percy. Not yet.

34:20.725 --> 34:23.827
The cars arrived at Bridlington
in the middle of the night,

34:23.862 --> 34:26.474
but nobody knows what's happened to Thomas.

34:26.498 --> 34:29.232
I've got an idea, sir.

34:29.266 --> 34:32.969
Why don't I go to the
mainland and look for Thomas?

34:33.004 --> 34:35.004
Wouldn't that be really useful?

34:35.039 --> 34:36.906
It's kind of you
to volunteer, James,

34:36.940 --> 34:39.809
but I need you to work
on Thomas's branch line.

34:39.844 --> 34:42.011
There are still carrots
waiting in Ulfstead

34:42.045 --> 34:43.980
and cars full of tweezers
in Vicarstown.

34:44.014 --> 34:47.050
But I <i> want</i> to go
to the mainland, sir.

34:47.085 --> 34:50.987
After all, I was the one who was
supposed to go, not Thomas.

34:51.022 --> 34:53.188
I've already sent Emily off
with the Kipper.

34:53.224 --> 34:55.458
- Uh, what about...
- And Edward is collecting the band.

34:55.493 --> 34:58.695
- I mean, someone...
- I simply can't spare another engine.

34:58.730 --> 35:01.197
- But I want to...
- Not with Henry at the Steamworks

35:01.232 --> 35:02.899
and Thomas delayed.

35:02.934 --> 35:06.603
Delayed? Oh, no!
I only thought he was lost.

35:06.638 --> 35:08.304
All done, sir.

35:08.339 --> 35:10.907
And I've made you
a fresh pot of tea.

35:10.942 --> 35:12.609
Oh, excellent. Thank you.

35:12.644 --> 35:15.111
Don't worry, Percy.

35:15.146 --> 35:17.313
Everything is under control.

35:17.348 --> 35:20.383
Just keep calm and carry on.

35:20.418 --> 35:22.819
At least you tried, James.

35:22.854 --> 35:26.623
Hmph. I'll never get to go
to the mainland now.

35:34.332 --> 35:39.502
Oh, this... is...
thirsty... work.

35:39.537 --> 35:43.873
That's what we've been trying to
tell you, little tank engine.

35:43.908 --> 35:47.076
This really is
the hottest place in town.

35:47.111 --> 35:51.080
My name is Thomas, Frankie.

35:51.115 --> 35:53.383
And you're doing a terrific job.

35:53.418 --> 35:56.452
Hurricane and I
are very impressed.

35:56.487 --> 35:58.354
And with you here to help us,

35:58.389 --> 36:01.691
we're free
to make more deliveries!

36:01.726 --> 36:05.828
It's not easy to keep up with all the
work here when it's only Frankie and me.

36:05.863 --> 36:08.598
We're both so happy
that you came along, Thomas.

36:08.633 --> 36:10.967
- Oh, thanks...
- Hurricane.

36:11.002 --> 36:12.835
This steel won't deliver itself.

36:12.870 --> 36:14.905
Bye, Thomas. See you later.

36:19.844 --> 36:21.878
Put the ingots
in the cooling area

36:21.913 --> 36:26.082
and make sure you empty <i>all</i> the slag
onto the slag heap, little tank engine.

36:26.117 --> 36:29.652
And when you've done all of that,
you can sort out cars in the yard.

36:29.687 --> 36:34.224
I expect them ready when we get
back to collect the next delivery.

36:34.259 --> 36:37.060
But I need to go home
to Sodor now, Frankie.

36:37.095 --> 36:39.829
No way, little tank engine.

36:39.864 --> 36:43.099
We helped you.
So you have to help us.

36:43.134 --> 36:45.635
But... I <i> have</i> been helping you.

36:45.670 --> 36:48.605
I've been working hard all day.

36:48.640 --> 36:50.640
Sir Topham Hatt will be
wondering where I am!

37:05.690 --> 37:10.159
♪ <i>How much longer</i>
<i>Will I have to stay here?</i> ♪

37:10.194 --> 37:14.197
♪ <i>One more day?</i>
<i>Or a month? Or a year?</i> ♪

37:14.232 --> 37:17.634
♪ <i>Far from everything</i>
<i>I've ever known</i> ♪

37:17.669 --> 37:21.671
♪ <i>Far away from the island</i>
<i>Called Sodor</i> ♪

37:21.706 --> 37:26.509
♪ <i>Far away from</i>
<i>That island called home</i> ♪

37:26.544 --> 37:30.446
♪ <i>Where are you</i>
<i>Annie and Clarabel?</i> ♪

37:30.481 --> 37:33.483
♪ <i>Have you been</i>
<i>Left in the shed?</i> ♪

37:33.518 --> 37:35.885
♪ <i>Or are you</i>
<i>Out on my branch line</i> ♪

37:35.920 --> 37:39.956
♪ <i>With some other engine</i>
<i>Instead?</i> ♪

37:39.991 --> 37:43.960
♪ <i>I miss all of my friends</i> ♪

37:43.995 --> 37:47.997
♪ <i>I miss hearing their names</i> ♪

37:48.032 --> 37:51.834
♪ <i>Percy and Toby and Gordon</i> ♪

37:51.869 --> 37:55.638
♪ <i>It's strange</i>
<i>But I even miss James</i> ♪

37:55.673 --> 37:59.509
♪ <i>I'm not joking</i>
<i>I even miss James</i> ♪

38:03.915 --> 38:08.017
♪ <i>I wanted to have</i>
<i>An adventure</i> ♪

38:08.052 --> 38:11.454
♪ <i>I wanted to wander and roam</i> ♪

38:11.489 --> 38:15.591
♪ <i>I wanted to see places</i>
<i>I'd never seen</i> ♪

38:15.626 --> 38:19.696
♪ <i>But now</i>
<i>I just want to go home</i> ♪

38:19.731 --> 38:23.833
♪ <i>Tell me</i>
<i>When do I get to go home?</i> ♪

38:35.413 --> 38:38.648
♪ <i>All I wanna do</i>
<i>Is go back to Sodor</i> ♪

38:38.683 --> 38:41.351
♪ <i>All I wanna do is get back</i>
<i>To my friends</i> ♪

38:41.386 --> 38:44.887
♪ <i>I don't wanna be stuck here</i>
<i>Forever and always</i> ♪

38:44.922 --> 38:47.990
♪ <i>In this hot house</i>
<i>Where work never ends</i> ♪

38:48.025 --> 38:51.260
♪ <i>I wanted adventure</i>
<i>I wanted to roam</i> ♪

38:51.295 --> 38:54.297
♪ <i>I wanted new places</i>
<i>But now I want home</i> ♪

38:54.332 --> 38:57.233
♪ <i>I mean it I have to go home</i> ♪

38:57.268 --> 39:00.636
♪ <i>So lock up your gates</i>
<i>With your skeleton key</i> ♪

39:00.671 --> 39:04.207
♪ <i>You can't make me stay</i>
<i>Where I don't want to be!</i> ♪

39:04.242 --> 39:06.409
♪ <i>It's not right It's not fair</i> ♪

39:06.444 --> 39:10.013
♪ <i>This is no place for me</i> ♪

39:13.484 --> 39:16.452
♪ <i>I want to, I need to</i> ♪

39:16.487 --> 39:21.891
♪ <i>I have to be free to go home</i> ♪

39:25.329 --> 39:28.197
♪ <i>I'll find my way home</i> ♪
Stop!

39:28.232 --> 39:31.667
Where are you going?
♪ <i>I'll make my way home</i> ♪

39:31.702 --> 39:34.837
♪ <i>It's time to go home</i> ♪

39:34.872 --> 39:39.309
♪ <i>I'm going home</i> ♪

39:51.022 --> 39:55.024
What am I supposed to do,
just sit here and do nothing?

39:55.059 --> 39:57.693
Yes, James.
That's what Thomas would do.

39:57.728 --> 40:00.363
Wait for the farmer.
What else can you do?

40:00.398 --> 40:02.698
I can blow my whistle.

40:02.733 --> 40:05.201
That'll get those sheep moving.
No!

40:05.236 --> 40:09.238
That's mean! You'll frighten
them, and they'll panic.

40:09.273 --> 40:13.309
Even Thomas is more
patient than you are, James.

40:13.344 --> 40:17.413
I've had enough. This is boring!

40:25.490 --> 40:27.089
See, James?

40:27.124 --> 40:30.793
All it takes
is a little patience.

40:30.828 --> 40:32.195
Baa.

40:45.510 --> 40:50.079
That was a close
call there, little tank engine.

40:50.114 --> 40:52.815
Yeah, you could have done yourself
some serious damage, Thomas,

40:52.850 --> 40:54.217
going off the rails like that.

40:56.254 --> 40:59.755
That old track
hasn't been used for years.

40:59.790 --> 41:02.158
And how would
we manage without you?

41:02.193 --> 41:06.362
You can't expect Hurricane and I to
be doing all of that dirty work.

41:06.397 --> 41:09.098
We have more important jobs
to be doing.

41:09.133 --> 41:12.635
I suppose so.

41:17.475 --> 41:22.478
<i>That night on Sodor,
James was more grumpy than ever.</i>

41:22.513 --> 41:27.617
I've had enough of being stuck on
Thomas's backwater branch line.

41:27.652 --> 41:29.752
I should be the one
on the mainland.

41:29.787 --> 41:31.888
Of course you should, James.

41:31.923 --> 41:34.056
Then you could be the one
who got lost.

41:35.793 --> 41:39.228
Or even worse, delayed.

41:39.263 --> 41:42.899
Hmph! I wouldn't get
lost <i>or</i> delayed.

41:42.934 --> 41:45.234
And if Thomas isn't
back here by morning,

41:45.269 --> 41:49.372
I'm going to the mainland to find
him and bring him back home.

41:49.407 --> 41:52.775
And who's going to look after all the
passengers on Thomas's branch line

41:52.810 --> 41:54.677
while you're gone, James?

41:54.712 --> 41:57.313
I don't know. Why don't
you ask Sir Topham Hatt?

41:57.348 --> 42:00.216
It's his job
to swap engines around.

42:00.251 --> 42:04.020
"That's what a
railway controller does."

42:04.055 --> 42:07.823
Oh, James. You'll be a hero!

42:10.428 --> 42:14.063
Only if he manages
to <i> find</i> Thomas.

42:17.702 --> 42:19.969
James. Wait!

42:20.004 --> 42:21.170
Where are you going?

42:21.205 --> 42:23.072
To the mainland.

42:23.107 --> 42:28.211
To find Thomas
and become... a hero!

43:42.219 --> 43:43.953
Shh.

43:55.433 --> 43:57.867
Oh! What was that?

43:57.902 --> 43:59.669
What was what?

43:59.704 --> 44:01.704
That big crashing sound.

44:01.739 --> 44:04.640
Maybe it was the thunder.

44:04.675 --> 44:07.910
There's a storm coming.

44:07.945 --> 44:08.945
Thomas?

44:11.248 --> 44:13.282
Thomas!

44:15.820 --> 44:18.221
He's trying to
break the gates down!

44:20.424 --> 44:22.992
No, Thomas! Don't do it!

44:23.027 --> 44:25.361
Stop, Thomas. Stop!

44:25.396 --> 44:27.030
Thomas!

44:32.737 --> 44:34.437
Come back!

44:41.312 --> 44:43.146
Oh, they're after me!

44:47.051 --> 44:48.484
Oh!

44:57.094 --> 44:59.195
Oh! Hurry up!

45:00.131 --> 45:01.397
They're coming.

45:02.633 --> 45:04.233
They're coming!

45:10.808 --> 45:12.642
They <i> are</i> chasing after me.

45:15.112 --> 45:17.113
Ooh.

45:17.148 --> 45:20.550
Are you... hiding?

45:21.285 --> 45:23.452
Who said that?

45:23.487 --> 45:27.089
Oh, don't be frightened.
I'm hiding too!

45:27.124 --> 45:28.891
I love hiding.

45:28.926 --> 45:31.194
But where are you?

45:32.096 --> 45:33.462
I can't see you.

45:33.497 --> 45:35.598
Of course you can't.

45:35.633 --> 45:38.634
That's because I'm such a good hider.

45:38.669 --> 45:42.037
In fact, I'm invisible!

45:43.641 --> 45:48.110
Invisible?
How can you be invisible?

45:48.145 --> 45:50.713
Because I'm a stealth engine.

45:50.748 --> 45:54.016
And stealth engines are designed
in a special way to make them...

45:54.051 --> 45:56.185
invisible.

45:56.220 --> 45:58.187
A stealth engine?

45:58.823 --> 46:01.290
Like... Merlin?

46:01.325 --> 46:06.295
Not <i> like</i> Merlin. I <i> am</i> Merlin.

46:06.330 --> 46:10.833
The experimental prototype, King
Arthur-class stealth engine.

46:10.868 --> 46:13.102
Merlin. Wow!

46:13.137 --> 46:15.304
Is that really you?

46:15.339 --> 46:17.473
I heard all about you from Theo
and Lexi and...

46:17.508 --> 46:19.742
Quick, close your eyes.

46:22.246 --> 46:25.515
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

46:34.992 --> 46:37.293
Don't worry. You're safe.

46:37.328 --> 46:38.661
They won't find you now.

46:38.696 --> 46:41.597
You're with the best hider ever.

46:41.632 --> 46:45.668
All you have to do is close
your eyes and keep really still,

46:45.703 --> 46:48.905
and nobody will be able
to see you.

47:04.922 --> 47:09.458
Hello? Merlin? Are you there?

47:09.493 --> 47:13.195
Oh, or are you still asleep?

47:13.230 --> 47:15.664
Sorry.

47:15.699 --> 47:19.302
Merlin? Merlin?

47:26.210 --> 47:30.379
<i>That morning, James had
arrived at Bridlington Goods Yard.</i>

47:30.414 --> 47:34.050
Thomas! Thomas!

47:39.690 --> 47:41.657
Excuse me.

47:41.692 --> 47:43.826
But have you, by any chance,

47:43.861 --> 47:48.964
seen a cheeky blue tank engine with
the number 1 painted on his side?

47:48.999 --> 47:52.801
We get a lot of engines
passing through.

47:52.836 --> 47:56.605
You can't expect me to remember
every blue tank engine.

47:56.640 --> 47:59.808
His name is Thomas,
from the Island of Sodor.

47:59.843 --> 48:04.213
Ulli! You seen a cheeky blue
tank engine, numbered 1?

48:05.616 --> 48:08.450
Nope. Like I say, friend.

48:08.485 --> 48:11.420
We get a lot of engines
coming and going.

48:11.455 --> 48:16.058
Bridlington is
a very busy goods yard.

48:16.093 --> 48:18.027
Oh, well.

48:18.062 --> 48:20.029
Thank you anyway.

48:20.798 --> 48:21.897
Psst.

48:21.932 --> 48:24.500
We saw a silly blue tank engine.

48:24.535 --> 48:27.703
Didn't know where he was going.

48:27.738 --> 48:31.807
- No sense.
- Of direction.

48:31.842 --> 48:35.844
Yes. Yes!
That sounds like Thomas.

48:35.879 --> 48:37.947
Is he the engine
that brought you here?

48:37.982 --> 48:41.283
- No!
- Don't be silly.

48:41.318 --> 48:43.686
Thomas got completely lost.

48:43.721 --> 48:46.655
An engine called Hurricane
brought us here.

48:46.690 --> 48:48.958
Hurricane? Who's Hurricane?

48:48.993 --> 48:52.261
From that big steelworks.
You know.

48:52.296 --> 48:55.264
♪ <i>This is the hottest place</i>
<i>In town</i> ♪

48:55.299 --> 48:58.134
♪ <i>We love an engine In an
evening gown</i> ♪

48:59.737 --> 49:02.638
This is hopeless.

49:02.673 --> 49:06.108
♪ <i>Look at my face</i>
<i>Don't I look like a clown?</i> ♪

49:06.143 --> 49:09.044
Well, he was a bit rude.

49:09.079 --> 49:11.947
Hello? One more question.

49:11.982 --> 49:16.686
Do you know a big steelworks where an
engine called Hurricane might be working?

49:27.998 --> 49:31.467
I know where I am.

49:31.502 --> 49:34.169
This is the experimental eng...
Theo.

49:34.204 --> 49:37.439
It's that engine again! Thomas!

49:37.474 --> 49:40.042
Well, hello, Thomas. Theo!

49:40.077 --> 49:41.510
Thomas!

49:47.718 --> 49:48.884
You came back.

49:48.919 --> 49:50.397
Did you get
where you were going?

49:50.421 --> 49:52.187
Did you find
what you were looking for?

49:52.222 --> 49:54.256
"Bridlingdom"? That goods yard?

49:54.291 --> 49:55.824
Did ya? Did ya?

49:55.859 --> 49:57.292
No.

49:57.327 --> 49:59.995
Oh. But you did deliver
your cars, didn't you?

50:00.030 --> 50:01.230
No.

50:01.265 --> 50:03.866
But where are they?
I don't see them. Huh?

50:03.901 --> 50:06.235
- Where'd they go?
- I don't know.

50:06.270 --> 50:08.504
He <i> is</i> being scrapped.
I told you.

50:08.539 --> 50:11.774
No, Theo.
I'm not being scrapped.

50:11.809 --> 50:15.311
But... I probably should be.

50:18.082 --> 50:20.849
Oh, Thomas. What happened?

50:20.884 --> 50:24.386
I lost James's cars, and I got
trapped in the steelworks,

50:24.421 --> 50:27.990
and I want to go home to Sodor,
but I don't know the way.

50:28.025 --> 50:30.626
I'm a useless engine.

50:30.661 --> 50:33.429
I just do everything wrong.

50:33.464 --> 50:35.864
- You sound like one of us.
- Yep.

50:35.899 --> 50:38.200
We have the same problem.

50:39.703 --> 50:43.305
No, you don't.
You guys are amazing.

50:43.340 --> 50:47.009
You're experimental engines.

50:47.044 --> 50:51.480
I can't do anything,
apart from make mistakes.

50:51.515 --> 50:55.017
Nobody gets it right
the first time.

50:55.052 --> 50:58.654
Everybody makes mistakes
or goofs or gaffes.

50:58.689 --> 51:02.658
♪ <i>We were put together</i>
<i>In a flurry of excitement</i> ♪

51:02.693 --> 51:04.359
♪ <i>But look at us now</i> ♪

51:04.394 --> 51:05.961
♪ <i>What are we like?</i> ♪
Ooh!

51:05.996 --> 51:07.429
♪ <i>You simply have to laugh</i> ♪

51:14.138 --> 51:17.873
♪ <i>We're unusual We're unique</i> ♪

51:17.908 --> 51:20.976
♪ <i>In other words She's
saying That we're freaks</i> ♪

51:21.011 --> 51:22.077
♪ <i>Built by geeks</i> ♪

51:22.112 --> 51:25.747
♪ <i>We're experiments gone bad</i> ♪

51:25.782 --> 51:29.418
♪ <i>In other words Whoever
designed us Must be mad</i> ♪

51:29.453 --> 51:33.622
♪ <i>Too many funnels</i>
<i>Or too many cogs</i> ♪

51:33.657 --> 51:37.192
♪ <i>We know a guy Who
was built to run on logs</i> ♪

51:37.227 --> 51:41.196
♪ <i>Too many wheels
And gears and rods</i> ♪

51:41.231 --> 51:44.967
♪ <i>It's no wonder That we
look so odd</i> ♪ Give me a prod.

51:45.002 --> 51:47.636
♪ <i>But what can't we do?</i> ♪

51:48.739 --> 51:50.806
♪ <i>What can't we do?</i> ♪

51:52.509 --> 51:54.510
♪ <i>What can't we do?</i> ♪

51:56.013 --> 51:58.114
♪ <i>Anything It's true</i> ♪

52:00.317 --> 52:04.153
♪ <i>We're originals</i>
<i>We're one of a kind</i> ♪

52:04.188 --> 52:07.890
♪ <i>We're upside down</i>
<i>And forward-to-behind</i> ♪

52:07.925 --> 52:11.693
♪ <i>We're experiments gone wrong</i> ♪

52:11.728 --> 52:14.130
♪ <i>This yard's the only place</i>
<i>That we could ever belong</i> ♪

52:15.666 --> 52:19.635
♪ <i>We always Try to do our best</i> ♪

52:19.670 --> 52:22.804
♪ <i>Sadly We rarely pass the
test</i> ♪ ♪ <i>I made a mess</i> ♪

52:22.839 --> 52:26.441
♪ <i>Give us a job Give us a task</i> ♪

52:26.476 --> 52:29.611
♪ <i>Whatever it is You'll
be sorry That you asked</i> ♪

52:29.646 --> 52:32.815
♪ <i>But what can't we do</i> ♪

52:33.984 --> 52:36.218
♪ <i>What can't we do?</i> ♪

52:37.454 --> 52:39.688
♪ <i>What can't we do?</i> ♪

52:41.024 --> 52:44.193
♪ <i>Anything It's true</i> ♪

52:44.228 --> 52:46.094
Ooh, ooh, ooh.
I can do something!

52:46.129 --> 52:48.097
Merlin?

52:50.834 --> 52:54.103
Invisibility on!

52:58.675 --> 53:00.242
♪ <i>I'm invisible</i> ♪

53:00.277 --> 53:02.211
♪ <i>Or can't you see?</i> ♪

53:02.246 --> 53:06.615
♪ <i>"Who said that?" you ask</i>
<i>It's only me</i> ♪

53:06.650 --> 53:10.586
♪ <i>You look surprised</i>
<i>But have no fear</i> ♪

53:10.621 --> 53:14.623
♪ <i>It's just a little trick</i>
<i>To make myself disappear</i> ♪

53:21.732 --> 53:24.600
Um, why does he keep doing that?

53:24.635 --> 53:27.369
Have you noticed
his three funnels?

53:27.404 --> 53:32.808
Well, that was an experiment... to
make his smoke and steam disperse,

53:32.843 --> 53:35.777
so you couldn't
see him so easily.

53:35.812 --> 53:38.413
But it didn't work at all.

53:38.448 --> 53:39.848
Only don't try and tell Merlin.

53:39.883 --> 53:40.816
Ah!

53:40.851 --> 53:42.951
Hello again.

53:42.986 --> 53:46.888
♪ <i>We're lumpy and bumpy</i>
<i>We haven't got the puff</i> ♪

53:46.923 --> 53:48.423
♪ <i>They tried to Make us better</i> ♪

53:48.458 --> 53:50.759
♪ <i>But sometimes</i>
<i>Enough's enough</i> ♪

53:50.794 --> 53:54.296
♪ <i>We're wobbly and knobbly</i>
<i>And awkward in reverse</i> ♪

53:54.331 --> 53:55.797
♪ <i>If practice</i>
<i>Makes you perfect</i> ♪

53:55.832 --> 53:58.867
♪ <i>We're the ones</i>
<i>They never rehearsed</i> ♪

53:58.902 --> 54:02.037
♪ <i>But what can't we do?</i> ♪

54:03.407 --> 54:05.407
♪ <i>What can't we do?</i> ♪

54:06.943 --> 54:09.111
♪ <i>What can't we do?</i> ♪

54:10.414 --> 54:12.948
♪ <i>Anything It's true</i> ♪

54:12.983 --> 54:14.883
♪ <i>We can't do anything</i> ♪

54:14.918 --> 54:16.818
♪ <i>That's true</i> ♪

54:16.853 --> 54:19.588
<i>-</i> ♪<i> We can't do anything</i> ♪
<i>-</i> ♪<i> But we can try</i> ♪

54:19.623 --> 54:23.592
♪ <i>We can give anything a try</i> ♪

54:23.627 --> 54:29.298
♪ <i>We will give anything a try</i> ♪

54:29.333 --> 54:32.401
Isn't that right?

54:36.506 --> 54:38.874
So do you think
you can try to help me?

54:38.909 --> 54:41.109
Didn't we just explain, Thomas?

54:41.144 --> 54:43.278
We can't do anything.

54:43.313 --> 54:45.947
Oh, stop saying that.

54:45.982 --> 54:49.284
We'll do everything we can
to help you, Thomas.

54:49.319 --> 54:51.086
Just tell us
what the problem is.

54:51.121 --> 54:53.088
Oh, Merlin, thank you!

54:53.123 --> 54:56.058
I need to go home
to the Island of Sodor.

54:56.093 --> 54:58.994
Only I don't know
which way to go.

54:59.029 --> 55:02.164
Merlin can't help you.
None of us can.

55:02.199 --> 55:03.865
I'm terribly sorry.

55:03.900 --> 55:07.402
We don't know anything about
anyplace other than here.

55:07.437 --> 55:11.840
Oh, but we can still try to
help you, Thomas. Oh, oh!

55:11.875 --> 55:13.208
We can go with you.

55:13.243 --> 55:17.379
And help you find the way
to the Island of Sonar!

55:17.414 --> 55:20.349
And then we'll
all get lost, Merlin.

55:20.384 --> 55:22.451
Or...

55:22.486 --> 55:25.587
you could always stay here with us,
Thomas, instead of going home.

55:25.622 --> 55:26.955
Thanks, Theo.

55:26.990 --> 55:29.291
Thanks all of you,
but I'll be all right.

55:29.326 --> 55:31.960
I'll find my way home...

55:31.995 --> 55:33.128
somehow.

55:34.264 --> 55:35.797
Bye, Thomas.

55:35.832 --> 55:37.733
Good luck. Oh.

55:40.070 --> 55:42.804
<i>Thomas headed back
along the branch line again,</i>

55:42.839 --> 55:45.708
<i>trying to remember the route
he'd taken before.</i>

55:46.710 --> 55:49.144
Mmm, this looks familiar.

55:50.347 --> 55:53.215
Oh, I think
I recognize this place.

55:53.250 --> 55:55.217
It looks like that canal I saw.

55:55.252 --> 55:57.052
Yes, it is!

55:57.087 --> 56:00.222
Oh, but there's
that silly crane.

56:00.257 --> 56:02.991
I really don't want him
to stop me again.

56:05.228 --> 56:08.430
Oh, no, you don't.

56:08.465 --> 56:09.998
Hey!

56:10.033 --> 56:12.667
You won't get past
so easily this time.

56:12.702 --> 56:16.271
What are you doing?
Stop that! Let go of me!

56:16.306 --> 56:18.106
Hello again, Thomas.

56:18.141 --> 56:22.210
Last time we met, you played a
cheeky trick on me and ran away.

56:22.245 --> 56:24.646
Just as we were getting
to know each other too.

56:24.681 --> 56:27.883
That wasn't a very nice way
to end our conversation.

56:27.918 --> 56:30.001
Picking up engines with
your hook is not a

56:30.013 --> 56:32.254
very nice way to start
a conversation either.

56:32.289 --> 56:35.657
Put me down! Please?

56:35.692 --> 56:39.761
And if I do put you down,
then what will you do, hmm?

56:39.796 --> 56:41.630
Run away again, no doubt.

56:41.665 --> 56:45.400
And I'll be left all on my own
again with nobody to talk to.

56:45.435 --> 56:49.438
Now, why don't you tell me
all about your adventures?

56:49.473 --> 56:51.840
My name's Beresford.
We could be friends.

56:51.875 --> 56:56.211
Look, I'm sorry I tricked you
last time, Beresford,

56:56.246 --> 57:00.882
but you can't just make somebody be your
friend by making them stay with you.

57:00.917 --> 57:04.486
You have to be nice to them
so they wanna be your friend.

57:05.222 --> 57:07.989
Now, put me down.

57:08.024 --> 57:11.993
Whoa!

57:12.028 --> 57:15.030
Hurricane!

57:15.065 --> 57:18.266
Pick me up, Beresford!
You have to hide me.

57:18.301 --> 57:20.969
Put you down? Pick you up?
Hide you?

57:21.004 --> 57:22.637
Make your mind up, Thomas.

57:22.672 --> 57:25.040
Hide me. Hide me! Please!

57:25.075 --> 57:26.675
I really need you to.

57:26.710 --> 57:28.410
Somewhere I can't be seen
from the tracks.

57:28.445 --> 57:29.711
Hurry!

57:30.480 --> 57:33.482
Whoa!

57:33.517 --> 57:36.885
Oh, yes. It's true.

57:36.920 --> 57:38.653
James.

57:38.688 --> 57:41.890
I am a particularly
useful engine.

57:41.925 --> 57:43.625
Is that right?

57:43.660 --> 57:49.097
In fact, back on Sodor, I am
Sir Topham Hatt's favorite.

57:50.901 --> 57:53.268
Okay, Thomas. They're all gone.

57:53.303 --> 57:55.971
And I did something
nice for you.

57:56.006 --> 57:58.373
So we can be friends now.

57:58.408 --> 57:59.441
What shall we talk about?

57:59.476 --> 58:02.644
James! They've got James!

58:02.679 --> 58:04.279
Who's James?

58:04.314 --> 58:06.147
Yes. Who's James?

58:06.182 --> 58:08.750
Merlin! What are you doing here?

58:08.785 --> 58:10.752
I followed you, Thomas.

58:10.787 --> 58:16.057
I'm here to look after you and make sure
you find your way safely back home.

58:16.092 --> 58:18.426
Excellent hiding, by the way.
Even I couldn't see you.

58:18.461 --> 58:20.829
But I can't go home now!

58:20.864 --> 58:23.231
I have to help my friend James!

58:23.266 --> 58:26.001
Why didn't you say something?
I could have stopped him.

58:27.070 --> 58:28.804
Oh!

58:30.340 --> 58:33.842
Oh! You have to let
me go now, Beresford.

58:33.877 --> 58:35.810
James is in trouble.

58:35.845 --> 58:40.181
If I hadn't taken his cars in the first
place, he wouldn't even be here.

58:40.216 --> 58:44.352
And now Hurricane and Frankie are
taking him to the steelworks.

58:44.387 --> 58:46.621
I have to rescue him.

58:46.656 --> 58:49.858
Don't you mean
<i>we</i> have to rescue him?

58:58.468 --> 59:02.237
♪ <i>This is the hottest place</i>
<i>In town</i> ♪

59:02.272 --> 59:05.173
♪ <i>We'll warm you up</i>
<i>When you're feeling down</i> ♪

59:05.208 --> 59:09.044
♪ <i>We'll make a smile</i>
<i>Out of every frown</i> ♪

59:09.079 --> 59:12.047
♪ <i>Just take a look around</i>
<i>At the joy we've found</i> ♪

59:12.082 --> 59:15.850
♪ <i>This is the place</i>
<i>You can have some fun</i> ♪

59:15.885 --> 59:18.787
♪ <i>Where you can feel</i>
<i>Like you're number one</i> ♪

59:18.822 --> 59:22.757
♪ <i>We've got more sunshine</i>
<i>Than the sun</i> ♪

59:22.792 --> 59:26.061
♪ <i>There's a light in our eyes</i>
<i>We simply can't disguise</i> ♪

59:26.096 --> 59:28.363
Huh? All right. All right.

59:28.398 --> 59:32.233
This is all very entertaining,
but where's Thomas?

59:32.268 --> 59:34.836
Uh, Thomas? Who's Thomas?

59:34.871 --> 59:39.374
He's a small blue tank engine
from the Island of Sodor.

59:39.409 --> 59:42.410
But I think you already
know that,

59:42.445 --> 59:45.580
because one of you
delivered his cars,

59:45.615 --> 59:46.748
Hurricane.

59:46.783 --> 59:48.883
- Uh, T-T...
- Oh, oh!

59:48.918 --> 59:50.652
<i>That</i> blue tank engine.

59:50.687 --> 59:52.153
He's long gone.

59:52.188 --> 59:53.888
But where did he go?

59:53.923 --> 59:55.757
- Anywhere.
- Everywhere.

59:55.792 --> 59:57.626
I think he wanted
to see the world.

59:57.661 --> 01:00:00.996
Well, I need to find him
and bring him back to Sodor.

01:00:01.031 --> 01:00:04.366
Of course, he did say
he was coming straight back.

01:00:04.401 --> 01:00:06.701
He wasn't going off
to see the whole world,

01:00:06.736 --> 01:00:08.069
just a bit of it.

01:00:08.104 --> 01:00:10.405
You might as well
wait here for him.

01:00:14.811 --> 01:00:16.745
And make yourself useful.

01:00:20.984 --> 01:00:22.617
<i>We</i> have to rescue him?

01:00:22.652 --> 01:00:25.487
What do you mean
we have to rescue him?

01:00:25.522 --> 01:00:27.756
We can't do anything.

01:00:27.791 --> 01:00:31.092
But we can try. We have to try.

01:00:31.127 --> 01:00:35.263
I don't know what I can do either,
Theo, but James is my friend.

01:00:35.298 --> 01:00:37.832
And Thomas is our friend.

01:00:37.867 --> 01:00:40.869
And friends help each other.

01:00:40.904 --> 01:00:42.281
- Yes, yes, but...
- Indeed we do.

01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:43.905
I certainly think so.

01:00:43.940 --> 01:00:47.208
This is the most excitement
I've had in...

01:00:47.243 --> 01:00:49.845
forever!

01:00:58.988 --> 01:01:02.424
So, how are we going
to rescue Thomas's friend?

01:01:02.459 --> 01:01:04.392
We need a plan.

01:01:04.427 --> 01:01:06.628
Thomas broke the gates open
before.

01:01:06.663 --> 01:01:08.697
That's the ticket.

01:01:08.732 --> 01:01:10.865
We could do the same thing.
Yeah.

01:01:10.900 --> 01:01:12.701
Or... and just hear me out...

01:01:12.736 --> 01:01:15.303
we could leave the gates
where they are.

01:01:15.338 --> 01:01:20.508
Oh! I can use the powers of stealth
to sneak in and rescue James.

01:01:20.543 --> 01:01:22.277
Nobody will see me.

01:01:22.312 --> 01:01:25.113
Invisibility on.

01:01:26.249 --> 01:01:28.349
Or...

01:01:28.384 --> 01:01:31.152
why don't Theo and Lexi
create a diversion?

01:01:31.187 --> 01:01:34.456
They could pretend to have
an accident and call for help,

01:01:34.491 --> 01:01:38.026
and while the gates are open,
I can rush in and rescue James.

01:01:38.061 --> 01:01:39.828
But what am I going to do?

01:01:39.863 --> 01:01:43.898
You'll have to stay back here
and keep watch, Merlin.

01:01:43.933 --> 01:01:47.635
Keeping watch is
the most important job of all.

01:01:47.670 --> 01:01:49.671
Oh, yes.

01:01:49.706 --> 01:01:51.673
C-Couldn't I stay back here too
and just watch?

01:01:51.708 --> 01:01:53.274
No, Theo.

01:01:53.309 --> 01:01:56.778
You and Lexi need to
create a conversion.

01:01:56.813 --> 01:01:58.813
I'm the one who's
going to keep watch.

01:01:58.848 --> 01:02:02.050
Come on, Theo! Oh.

01:02:02.085 --> 01:02:03.818
Don't worry, Thomas.

01:02:03.853 --> 01:02:06.020
Those two are bound
to be a little nervous.

01:02:06.055 --> 01:02:09.124
They're not as used to
having adventures as we are.

01:02:11.127 --> 01:02:14.662
I think I can't. I think I can't.
I know I can't.

01:02:14.697 --> 01:02:16.664
Whoa! Speed up, Theo.

01:02:16.699 --> 01:02:19.267
Move along, move along.
You need to go fast.

01:02:21.905 --> 01:02:24.806
Now, Theo! Stop!

01:02:29.646 --> 01:02:32.080
What was that? I don't know.

01:02:32.115 --> 01:02:33.648
Help! Help!

01:02:33.683 --> 01:02:35.984
There's been a derailment!

01:02:36.019 --> 01:02:40.021
Engine off the line!
Emergency! Emergency!

01:03:03.446 --> 01:03:04.446
James.

01:03:06.316 --> 01:03:07.616
James.

01:03:08.518 --> 01:03:11.219
James! Where are you?

01:03:13.489 --> 01:03:16.691
Oh, no! What's happened?

01:03:16.726 --> 01:03:21.396
- Has someone fallen to pieces?
- Have you had an accident?

01:03:21.431 --> 01:03:26.434
You look kind of messed up, like your
pistons are in the wrong places.

01:03:26.469 --> 01:03:29.037
Hmm, I'm confused.

01:03:29.072 --> 01:03:31.840
I thought somebody said
there had been a derailment.

01:03:31.875 --> 01:03:34.543
Um...

01:03:36.713 --> 01:03:38.446
This is taking too long.

01:03:38.481 --> 01:03:40.882
T-Thomas should have
been out by now.

01:03:40.917 --> 01:03:42.750
Ah! I hope nothing's
happened to him.

01:03:42.785 --> 01:03:45.386
What if he needs my help?

01:03:45.421 --> 01:03:48.890
Invisibility on!

01:03:48.925 --> 01:03:54.095
Ah, oh, well,
there was a kind of derailment.

01:03:54.130 --> 01:03:56.197
Lexi! Bit of an accident.

01:03:56.232 --> 01:03:58.967
Came off the rails.
Whoopsy! He fell right over.

01:03:59.002 --> 01:04:02.403
Merlin?
Lexi!

01:04:02.438 --> 01:04:05.607
Wait a minute! Where's he going?

01:04:05.642 --> 01:04:07.842
Whoa! Stop!

01:04:07.877 --> 01:04:11.213
Ohh!

01:04:16.119 --> 01:04:22.023
Oh, all this soot, ash and heat
will positively ruin my paintwork.

01:04:22.058 --> 01:04:25.159
This is a horrible job for an
engine like... James.

01:04:25.194 --> 01:04:29.697
James. Oh, so there you are!

01:04:29.732 --> 01:04:32.800
What do you think you've
been playing at? James.

01:04:32.835 --> 01:04:36.037
Keep your voice down. First you
take my cars to the mainland.

01:04:36.072 --> 01:04:39.908
I'll explain later, James.
We really need to go.

01:04:39.943 --> 01:04:42.911
- Oh, I'm more than ready to go.
- James.

01:04:42.946 --> 01:04:45.947
I'd already decided that I was
just going to do this one job.

01:04:45.982 --> 01:04:48.349
It doesn't work like that,
James.

01:04:48.384 --> 01:04:51.686
Frankie and Hurricane
won't <i> let</i> you leave.

01:04:51.721 --> 01:04:55.023
Thomas. You need to hurry!

01:04:55.058 --> 01:04:58.693
They're coming back!
They're coming back!

01:04:59.195 --> 01:05:00.729
Thomas!

01:05:02.231 --> 01:05:03.598
They're back.

01:05:03.633 --> 01:05:06.401
Quick, James! We've got to
get out of here now!

01:05:06.436 --> 01:05:08.436
Go!

01:05:08.471 --> 01:05:12.173
Stop! You
can't leave us on our own!

01:05:12.208 --> 01:05:14.609
Aaah! No.

01:05:14.644 --> 01:05:16.044
Look out!

01:05:17.947 --> 01:05:20.481
Take the tracks that go
around the building, James!

01:05:22.518 --> 01:05:24.119
Ohh!

01:05:29.892 --> 01:05:31.459
Oh!

01:05:31.494 --> 01:05:33.461
We can't just let you leave.

01:05:33.496 --> 01:05:36.764
You're our favorite new engine!
Leave me alone!

01:05:45.675 --> 01:05:48.510
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

01:05:53.483 --> 01:05:56.117
Found you!

01:05:57.420 --> 01:06:02.156
Whoa!

01:06:03.659 --> 01:06:06.828
Whoa!

01:06:08.531 --> 01:06:11.032
Oh, no!
Yeah.

01:06:11.067 --> 01:06:13.401
Whoa!

01:06:13.436 --> 01:06:15.770
Oh, no, you don't!

01:06:15.805 --> 01:06:18.406
- What?
- Go, James, go!

01:06:29.519 --> 01:06:30.685
Ohh!

01:06:30.720 --> 01:06:33.888
Run away! Scram! Skedaddle!

01:06:41.798 --> 01:06:44.432
Help! Help!

01:06:44.467 --> 01:06:47.936
Whoa!

01:06:50.273 --> 01:06:54.175
- No!
- Don't worry. I'll get you down, Thomas.

01:06:54.210 --> 01:06:56.011
No!

01:07:08.391 --> 01:07:11.793
Thomas! Look out!

01:07:11.828 --> 01:07:15.897
Help! My front wheels!
I'm melting!

01:07:15.932 --> 01:07:17.465
I'm melting!

01:07:17.500 --> 01:07:20.301
Oh, Hurricane!

01:07:20.336 --> 01:07:24.105
What should I do? Anything!

01:07:26.042 --> 01:07:28.009
Whoo-hoo.

01:07:29.679 --> 01:07:31.479
Oh!

01:07:31.514 --> 01:07:35.483
Hurricane can't make deliveries
with melted wheels,

01:07:35.518 --> 01:07:37.285
and now you're
all going to go away

01:07:37.320 --> 01:07:40.288
and leave us on our own
with no help at all!

01:07:40.323 --> 01:07:43.791
It serves you right, after all the
things you've done to Thomas.

01:07:43.826 --> 01:07:47.061
Aye. Keeping him here
when he wanted to go home.

01:07:47.096 --> 01:07:48.963
And trying to trick his friend.

01:07:48.998 --> 01:07:52.634
But... But...

01:07:54.203 --> 01:07:57.371
Frankie, are you all right?

01:07:57.406 --> 01:08:00.174
We only wanted some help.

01:08:00.209 --> 01:08:04.479
There's too much work
for just the two of us.

01:08:04.514 --> 01:08:07.048
But why didn't you ask for help?

01:08:07.083 --> 01:08:09.951
Nobody wants to work here.

01:08:09.986 --> 01:08:13.387
All the other engines
are too busy to help us.

01:08:13.422 --> 01:08:16.756
Don't cry, Frankie.

01:08:16.792 --> 01:08:19.660
Maybe some engines
aren't as busy as you think.

01:08:19.694 --> 01:08:22.330
What? What do you mean?

01:08:24.133 --> 01:08:26.300
Wait? Us? I don't think so!

01:08:26.335 --> 01:08:28.469
Nope. Nope. No sirree, Bob.

01:08:28.504 --> 01:08:30.671
We're really useless engines.

01:08:30.706 --> 01:08:34.008
Useless? You're not useless.

01:08:34.042 --> 01:08:36.243
No engine is useless.

01:08:36.279 --> 01:08:38.379
Didn't you just help me
rescue James?

01:08:38.413 --> 01:08:40.281
Think positively, Lexi.

01:08:40.316 --> 01:08:42.683
Ask yourself what <i> can</i> you do?

01:08:42.718 --> 01:08:45.586
You mean anything?

01:08:45.621 --> 01:08:48.221
No, uh, we can't do anything.

01:08:48.256 --> 01:08:50.792
But we can try.

01:08:54.130 --> 01:08:58.399
<i>So Thomas and James
headed back to Sodor together.</i>

01:08:58.434 --> 01:09:02.203
I'm sorry I took your cars,
James.

01:09:02.238 --> 01:09:05.305
